From 59be8dbc81a8fdfcdc9b881e97f54e43dc0277b6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brandon Thompson <brandon.joseph.thompson@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 18:38:39 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Patch: Add process-spawn visibility to Ryoku Shell.

Centralizes every process spawn across the shell, ryowalls, hub, ryovm, and
the lockscreen behind a shared Spawn wrapper (ryoku/shared/quickshell/) that
captures stdout/stderr to a log file, deletes it on a clean exit, and fires a
desktop notification with a "View log" action on failure. The launcher's own
copy additionally tracks a live registry so search results can show
"(N launched)" next to the app name and "View log(s)" appears in the Ctrl+K
action panel for anything still running or that failed.

Fixes two related pre-existing bugs surfaced by wiring notification-center
clicks through the new wrapper: activateEntry()'s window-focus script
returned a spurious failure exit code whenever the clicked notification's
sender had no matching window (a normal, common case), and the Inbox's group
header could re-display a critical notification's own content a second time
when it had nothing else to preview.
